Static-source inventory of fraiseql-observers and the binary's
observer subsystem against the phase-doc Cycle 3 "New" list. Citation
candidates for the GREEN Writer are included inline.

## Crate layout

  $ git ls-tree -r d0a4ed4ec | grep -E 'crates/fraiseql-observers/' | wc -l
  104

`fraiseql-observers` is large (104 files, of which 80+ under `src/`).
The crate's `lib.rs` documents the architecture in its module rustdoc
(`crates/fraiseql-observers/src/lib.rs:L1-L45`).

## TOML configuration shape (binary-wired)

`fraiseql-server::ServerConfig::observers: Option<ObserverConfig>`
(`crates/fraiseql-server/src/server_config/mod.rs:L440-L443`).

`ObserverConfig` (`crates/fraiseql-server/src/server_config/observers.rs:L94-L130`):
- `enabled: bool` (default `true`)
- `poll_interval_ms: u64` (default `100`)
- `batch_size: usize` (default `100`)
- `channel_capacity: usize` (default `1000`)
- `auto_reload: bool` (default `true`)
- `reload_interval_secs: u64` (default `60`)
- `pool: ObserverPoolConfig` (`:L42-L83`)
  - `min_connections: u32` (default `2`)
  - `max_connections: u32` (default `5`)
  - `acquire_timeout_secs: u64` (default `10`)

There is no `backend`, `redis_url`, `nats_url`, or `handlers` field on
`ObserverConfig`. Unknown TOML fields are silently dropped — `ServerConfig`
does not carry `#[serde(deny_unknown_fields)]`
(`crates/fraiseql-server/src/server_config/mod.rs:L40-L42`).

## Library-API (fraiseql-observers) configuration shape

`fraiseql-observers::ObserverRuntimeConfig`
(`crates/fraiseql-observers/src/config/runtime.rs:L13-L73`):
- `transport: TransportConfig` (`config/transport.rs:L48-L73`)
  - `transport: TransportKind` (default `Postgres`; variants
    `Postgres`, `Nats`, `InMemory` — `transport.rs:L15-L26`)
  - `run_bridge: bool`
  - `run_executors: bool` (default `true`)
  - `nats: NatsTransportConfig` (gated on `nats` feature)
  - `bridge: BridgeTransportConfig`
- `redis: Option<RedisConfig>` (gated on Redis features)
- `clickhouse: Option<ClickHouseConfig>`
- `job_queue: Option<JobQueueConfig>`
- `performance: PerformanceConfig`
- `channel_capacity: usize` (default `1000`)
- `max_concurrency: usize` (default `50`)
- `overflow_policy: OverflowPolicy` (default `Drop`; variants
  `Drop`, `Block`, `DropOldest` — `runtime.rs:L113-L122`)
- `backlog_alert_threshold: usize` (default `500`)
- `shutdown_timeout: String` (default `"30s"`)
- `max_dlq_size: Option<usize>` (default `None` = unbounded)
- `observers: HashMap<String, ObserverDefinition>` (`runtime.rs:L132-L145`)

`ObserverDefinition` (`runtime.rs:L132-L160`):
- `event_type: String` (e.g. `INSERT|UPDATE|DELETE|CUSTOM`)
- `entity: String`
- `condition: Option<String>` (Elo DSL)
- `actions: Vec<ActionConfig>`
- `retry: RetryConfig`
- `on_failure: FailurePolicy`

`ActionConfig` is a tagged union (`#[non_exhaustive]`, tag = "type",
snake_case — `runtime.rs:L260-L350`):
- `Webhook { url, url_env, headers, body_template }`
- `Slack { webhook_url, webhook_url_env, channel, message_template }`
- `Email { to, to_template, subject, subject_template, body_template, reply_to }`
- `Sms { phone, phone_template, message_template }` (stub)
- `Push { device_token, title_template, body_template }` (stub)
- `Search { index, id_template }` (stub)
- `Cache { key_pattern, action }` (stub)

`RetryConfig` (`runtime.rs:L170-L220`):
- `max_attempts: u32` (default `3`)
- `initial_delay_ms: u64` (default `100`)
- `max_delay_ms: u64` (default `30000`)
- `backoff_strategy: BackoffStrategy` (default `Exponential`;
  variants `Exponential|Linear|Fixed`)

`FailurePolicy` (`runtime.rs:L243-L255`): `Log` (default) | `Alert` | `Dlq`.

## fraiseql-cli TOML-validation schema (different shape, NOT runtime)

`fraiseql-cli::ObserversConfig`
(`crates/fraiseql-cli/src/config/toml_schema/observers.rs:L1-L55`).
This is the shape the four current docs pages describe. The CLI uses it
when compiling the user's source TOML for schema validation; the
server binary's `ServerConfig` parser does NOT use this schema and does
NOT translate `[[observers.handlers]]` into runtime observer registrations.

## Binary wiring (does the off-the-shelf binary do it?)

Yes — the off-the-shelf binary auto-instantiates the observer runtime when
`feature = "observers"` is built in (which the docs-test image is). The
wiring is at:

- `fraiseql-server::Server::init_observer_runtime`
  (`crates/fraiseql-server/src/server/extensions.rs:L362-L389`).
- `fraiseql-server::Server::build_observer_pool` reads `[observers.pool]`
  from `ServerConfig` (`crates/fraiseql-server/src/server/extensions.rs:
  L273-L308`).
- `fraiseql-server::Server::from_executor` calls `init_observer_runtime`
  unconditionally when `feature = "observers"` is enabled
  (`crates/fraiseql-server/src/server/builder.rs:L343-L346`).
- Routes are mounted in
  `crates/fraiseql-server/src/server/routing/observers.rs:L18-L66`:
  - `app.nest("/api/observers", observer_routes(...))` — CRUD over
    observer definitions, backed by `tb_observer` table.
  - `app.nest("/api/observers", observer_changelog_routes(...))` —
    `GET /api/observers/changelog`, `GET|PUT /api/observers/checkpoint/{id}`.
  - `app.merge(observer_runtime_routes(...))` — `/runtime/health`,
    `/runtime/reload` at the router ROOT (NOT nested under `/api/observers`).
  - `app.nest("/api/observers", observer_dlq_routes(...))` —
    `/delivery/health`, `/dlq`, `/dlq/retry-all`, `/dlq/{id}`,
    `/dlq/{id}/retry`.

This is DIFFERENT from multi-tenancy (FW-3) and storage (FW-7) — there the
binary fails to wire the subsystem. Observers IS auto-wired. But:

- The observer-definition store is `tb_observer`, a DB table not auto-
  migrated by the binary (`crates/fraiseql-observers/migrations/
  06_create_observer_management.sql`).
- The TOML shape the user-facing docs advertise (`backend`/`handlers`)
  is for the CLI validation schema, NOT the runtime.

So the docs-page failure for observers is NOT a binary-wiring failure —
it's a documented-TOML-shape failure (the docs describe `[[handlers]]`,
the binary's TOML schema doesn't have it) AND a missing-bootstrap-step
failure (the docs don't explain that `tb_observer` and the DLQ schema
must be installed by hand).

## Phase-doc Cycle 3 "New" list — confirm/refute matrix

| Phase-doc bullet | Status | Where it lives | Notes |
|------------------|--------|----------------|-------|
| `[observers]` TOML section | PARTIAL (drift) | `server_config/observers.rs:L94-L130` | Real, but missing `backend`/`redis_url`/`nats_url`/`handlers`. Different shape than docs say. |
| Backends: in-memory | CONFIRMED | `config/transport.rs:L15-L26` (`TransportKind::InMemory`) | Library-API; not selectable via binary's `[observers]`. |
| Backends: NATS | CONFIRMED | `config/transport.rs:L15-L26`, `transport/nats.rs:L1` | Behind `observers-nats` feature on `fraiseql-server`. |
| Backends: Redis | REFUTED | n/a | Redis is not an event transport. It's CACHE / DEDUP / JOB-QUEUE / LEASE (`Cargo.toml:L52-L68`). |
| Backends: PostgreSQL | CONFIRMED | `config/transport.rs:L15-L26` (`TransportKind::Postgres` is default), `transport/postgres_notify.rs:L1` | Polls `tb_entity_change_log`. |
| Backends: MySQL | REFUTED-as-stated | `transport/mysql_bridge.rs:L1-L31` | MySQL exists ONLY as a *bridge* (MySQL → NATS), not as a transport. |
| Feature flag `observers` | CONFIRMED | `fraiseql-server/Cargo.toml:L171-L172` | Maps to `dep:fraiseql-observers`. |
| Feature flag `observers-nats` | CONFIRMED | `fraiseql-server/Cargo.toml:L176` | Maps to `observers + fraiseql-observers/nats`. |
| Feature flag `observers-enterprise` | CONFIRMED | `fraiseql-server/Cargo.toml:L175` | Maps to `observers + fraiseql-observers/{enterprise, nats}`; the `enterprise` bundle is `["checkpoint", "dedup", "caching", "queue", "search", "metrics"]` (`fraiseql-observers/Cargo.toml:L57`). NOT "cross-instance HA" by itself — the HA primitive is `redis-lease`, which is in the `enterprise` bundle indirectly via `caching` ( ← `redis`). Worth a precise callout. |
| Action: webhook (retry / DLQ) | CONFIRMED | `actions.rs:L1-L43`, `executor/retry.rs:L17-L80`, `traits.rs::DeadLetterQueue` | SSRF protection in `actions.rs:L33-L45` is real. |
| Action: NATS publish | INFERRED — not an `ActionConfig` variant | `transport/nats.rs` | NATS is a TRANSPORT, not an action. The Cycle-3-spec line is mis-classified — NATS publish is the event-source side, not the action side. The runtime publishes events to NATS via the bridge; user code does not configure NATS publish per-action. |
| Action: email | CONFIRMED | `runtime.rs:L290-L308` (`ActionConfig::Email`), `actions.rs::EmailAction` | |
| Action: custom | PARTIAL | n/a as `ActionConfig` variant | `ActionConfig` is `#[non_exhaustive]` (`runtime.rs:L262`) — custom actions are not pluggable; "custom" means new variants in future minor versions, not user-defined types. |
| Observer changelog handlers (v2.3) | CONFIRMED | `crates/fraiseql-server/src/observers/changelog_handlers/mod.rs`, mounted at `/api/observers/changelog` and `/api/observers/checkpoint/{id}` (`server/routing/observers.rs:L43-L44`) | CHANGELOG cites #316/#317 axum 0.8 fix. |
| DLQ handlers (v2.3) | CONFIRMED | `crates/fraiseql-server/src/observers/dlq_handlers/mod.rs`, mounted at `/api/observers/dlq` etc. (`server/routing/observers.rs:L58-L65`) | |
| Lifecycle: subscription | CONFIRMED | `listener/change_log.rs`, `listener/coordinator.rs`, `listener/lease.rs:L1-L18`, `listener/failover.rs` | |
| Lifecycle: dispatch | CONFIRMED | `executor/dispatch.rs:L1-L60`, `executor/mod.rs`, `executor/actions.rs` | |
| Lifecycle: retry strategy | CONFIRMED | `executor/retry.rs:L1-L80` (exponential/linear/fixed with jitter via `rand`), `config/runtime.rs::RetryConfig` (`L170-L220`) | |
| Lifecycle: DLQ behaviour | CONFIRMED | `traits.rs::DeadLetterQueue`, `job_queue/dlq.rs::DeadLetterQueueManager`, in-memory DLQ in `fraiseql-server/src/observers/runtime.rs::InMemoryDlq` | |
| `entity_type_index` atomicity (F056) | CONFIRMED | `crates/fraiseql-server/src/observers/runtime.rs:L18 (use arc_swap::ArcSwap;)`, L139 (field), L164 (init), L300 (atomic swap), CHANGELOG L347-L358 | Reference: F006/F007/F008/F013/F048/F056/F057 batch. |
| Cross-instance HA via `observers-enterprise` | NUANCED | `listener/lease.rs:L1-L18` lists three lease backends: in-process, postgres advisory lock, redis SET NX EX. The `redis-lease` feature is in the `enterprise` bundle transitively (`caching` → `redis`). The phase-doc line "cross-instance HA via observers-enterprise" is *technically* true via the redis-lease backend but the binary on default features uses an in-process lease (no HA). |
| Worker panic propagation (F014) | CONFIRMED | `crates/fraiseql-observers/src/job_queue/executor.rs:L129-L188`, CHANGELOG L226-L228 (F014). Panics are caught at the JoinHandle layer, logged at `error!`, and counted by the metrics registry. |

## Drifted bullets — items in scope but not in the phase-doc Cycle 3 New list

The phase-doc's "New" list under-specifies several reader-critical surfaces:

- **`tb_observer` schema bootstrap** — observers live in the DB; the migration
  is at `crates/fraiseql-observers/migrations/06_create_observer_management.sql`
  and is NOT auto-applied. Without it, the binary errors at startup with
  `relation "tb_observer" does not exist` and runs `degraded`.
- **DLQ schema bootstrap** — separate migration at
  `crates/fraiseql-observers/migrations/01_create_dlq_schema.sql`.
- **Observer checkpoint store** — `migrations/02_create_observer_checkpoints.sql`
  is required if observers are polling `tb_entity_change_log` across restarts.
- **NATS transport additional migrations** —
  `migrations/03_add_nats_transport.sql`, `04_add_mysql_nats_transport.sql`,
  `05_add_mssql_nats_transport.sql`.
- **HTTP API for creating observers** —
  `POST /api/observers` with the request shape in
  `crates/fraiseql-server/src/observers/handlers.rs` is the documented way
  to install an observer at runtime. None of the four current pages mention
  this endpoint.
- **`fraiseql-observers` CLI binary** — separate from `fraiseql-cli`; behind
  the `cli` feature flag of `fraiseql-observers`; DLQ subcommands return
  hard-coded mock data (`crates/fraiseql-observers/src/cli/commands/dlq.rs:L38-L80`).
- **Per-handler webhook timeout & SSRF allowlist** — webhook URLs are
  validated against SSRF (loopback, RFC 1918, link-local, ULA) at dispatch
  time (`crates/fraiseql-observers/src/actions.rs:L33-L45`,
  `ssrf.rs:L1`). Default 30-second timeout (`actions.rs:L20-L23`).
- **`/health` degraded semantics** — `/health` returns
  `{"status":"degraded", "observers":{"running":false,...}}` when the runtime
  failed to start. None of the four pages document this.
- **Route-mount inconsistency** — `/runtime/health` and `/runtime/reload`
  are at the router ROOT, not under `/api/observers` like the other observer
  routes. Likely a bug; needs FW-13.

